1
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:39,240
[Episode 2: How many thousands of kalpas of time can a luxury watch count?]
(T/N: Kalpa is a long period of time, eons, in Buddhism)

2
00:00:39,240 --> 00:00:41,050
[Episode 2]

3
00:00:41,050 --> 00:00:44,090
You cooked delicious food and are even washing the dishes.

4
00:00:44,090 --> 00:00:46,880
You really don't have to do this.

5
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:49,160
Usually, cooking begins with preparing the ingredients

6
00:00:49,160 --> 00:00:52,310
and ends with washing the dishes.

7
00:00:52,310 --> 00:00:56,990
Oh! Did you know that Da Vinci originally dreamed of becoming a chef?

8
00:00:57,800 --> 00:01:00,040
[Da Vinci Restaurant?]

9
00:01:00,040 --> 00:01:02,670
Is that so?

10
00:01:02,670 --> 00:01:06,260
He even opened a restaurant. It's called "Three Frogs Flag Restaurant."

11
00:01:06,260 --> 00:01:09,460
- He didn't open it in Korea, right?
- Sorry?

12
00:01:09,460 --> 00:01:12,250
If he opened it in Korea, I would know.

13
00:01:12,250 --> 00:01:16,420
Even though I look like this, I am a board member of the Korean Restaurant Association.

14
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:23,910
Mr. Jin, you are so funny.

15
00:01:23,910 --> 00:01:28,270
How can you make a joke with such a serious face?

16
00:01:28,270 --> 00:01:29,770
I wasn't joking though.

17
00:01:29,770 --> 00:01:32,680
I'm a serious and reserved type of person.

18
00:01:33,690 --> 00:01:35,790
There you go again...

19
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:40,360
I'm going crazy.

20
00:01:40,360 --> 00:01:43,630
Why am I so drunk when I didn't even drink?

21
00:01:43,630 --> 00:01:45,710
What did you say?

22
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:50,580
I mean, we were strangers until yesterday.

23
00:01:50,580 --> 00:01:54,600
Today we even ate together, talked,

24
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,130
and laughed together.

25
00:01:56,130 --> 00:01:59,660
All of this feels weird. It's like a dream.

26
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:02,350
Is it because of the time difference?

27
00:02:02,350 --> 00:02:04,720
It isn't an ordinary fate.

28
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:10,440
According to the Mahayana Buddhist Vinaya Sutra, three thousand kalpas have gone by for us to meet.

29
00:02:11,270 --> 00:02:12,850
Us?

30
00:02:12,850 --> 00:02:17,840
In Buddhism, people's relationships are divided into time units called kalpas.

31
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:20,600
The time it takes

32
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:22,450
to get rid of a rock the size of a house

33
00:02:22,450 --> 00:02:25,060
by water dripping on it every hundred years

34
00:02:25,060 --> 00:02:27,010
is one "kalpa."

35
00:02:27,010 --> 00:02:29,960
It took 3,000 eons

36
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:32,210
for us to meet and spend one night together

37
00:02:32,210 --> 00:02:34,610
in this place.

38
00:02:34,610 --> 00:02:37,710
That's how precious our connection is.

39
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,800
I see.

40
00:02:48,390 --> 00:02:50,840
Is there anything I can do to help?

41
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:53,600
No, it's okay.

42
00:03:06,860 --> 00:03:09,820
3,000 eons...

43
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:42,420
What happened?

44
00:03:43,010 --> 00:03:44,600
What's going on?

45
00:03:51,570 --> 00:03:53,230
Miss Dali?

46
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:58,620
Miss Dali! What happened?

47
00:03:58,620 --> 00:04:01,060
What's going on? Where are you?

48
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:08,020
Miss Dali. Miss Dali.

49
00:04:08,660 --> 00:04:10,090
Miss Da... ? Miss Dali?

50
00:04:14,380 --> 00:04:17,540
Miss Dali.

51
00:04:17,540 --> 00:04:19,780
Miss Dali.

52
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:23,400
Miss Da–

53
00:04:43,140 --> 00:04:46,370
♫ I keep getting excited ♫

54
00:04:46,370 --> 00:04:51,410
♫ I love you, love you, love you, I’m only thinking about you again ♫

55
00:04:51,410 --> 00:04:54,400
♫ I keep getting nervous ♫

56
00:04:55,940 --> 00:04:59,950
It must have been a blackout. Sometimes this happens.

57
00:04:59,950 --> 00:05:02,660
Are you hurt anywhere?

58
00:05:02,660 --> 00:05:05,640
No. What about you, Mr. Jin?

59
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:07,070
I'm fine, too.

60
00:05:07,070 --> 00:05:11,330
♫ It shines like the moon that rises high in the night sky ♫

61
00:05:11,330 --> 00:05:12,510
You're heavy.

62
00:05:12,510 --> 00:05:15,140
Oh!

63
00:05:17,290 --> 00:05:19,200
Wa-wait a moment.

64
00:05:19,970 --> 00:05:22,420
- Please, close your e-eyes.
- My eyes?

65
00:05:22,420 --> 00:05:27,160
- Eyes.
- Ey-Ey-Eyes.

66
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:30,440
Please don't open them at all until I'm out of the room.

67
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:31,890
- Make sure you don't, please.
- All right.

68
00:05:31,890 --> 00:05:34,240
You can't open your eyes.

69
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:37,180
- Don't open your ey-eyes.
- All right.

70
00:05:38,450 --> 00:05:40,720
Don't open your eyes.

71
00:05:47,460 --> 00:05:50,490
♫ Ringing throughout the streets ♫

72
00:05:50,490 --> 00:05:55,360
♫ Is a song from our past, I want to listen to it with you, yeah ♫

73
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:58,400
♫ You fill my heart ♫

74
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:02,960
♫ Even your smallest breath makes me feel your preciousness ♫

75
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:05,520
♫ You're like a rainbow ♫

76
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:09,230
Why am I ashamed? I didn't do anything. Did something happen?

77
00:06:09,230 --> 00:06:12,830
No, not at all. I was cool. I was great.

78
00:06:12,830 --> 00:06:15,110
I was great.

79
00:06:16,420 --> 00:06:18,770
That's cold. It's cold.

80
00:06:28,210 --> 00:06:30,010
Okay, all right.

81
00:06:31,130 --> 00:06:34,600
Yes, I understand. I'll see you in a few.

82
00:06:39,350 --> 00:06:41,310
What did they say?

83
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:50,220
What? Did they say they're going to file a lawsuit?

84
00:06:51,060 --> 00:06:54,540
Is she insisting that the fake painting is real?

85
00:06:56,330 --> 00:06:57,510
Don't worry.

86
00:06:57,510 --> 00:07:01,210
I'll do whatever it takes so that I won't cause you any harm.

87
00:07:01,210 --> 00:07:03,150
Our company's lawyers are good.

88
00:07:03,150 --> 00:07:05,910
I pay them a lot of money, it's terrifying.

89
00:07:05,910 --> 00:07:10,030
Madam Bronckhorst asked me to tell you,

90
00:07:12,590 --> 00:07:15,130
thank you.

91
00:07:17,170 --> 00:07:18,750
To me?

92
00:07:18,750 --> 00:07:23,230
She had not paid for the painting in full, but thanks to you, she found out that it was a forgery.

93
00:07:23,230 --> 00:07:25,220
It does not look like she is going to let the situation go out of hand by suing you.

94
00:07:25,220 --> 00:07:28,500
She must have assessed that it would not do her any good to let this matter go any further.

95
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:31,050
Otherwise, she might become suspicious of all her other paintings.

96
00:07:31,050 --> 00:07:33,040
Oh.

97
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:35,610
The problem is Mr. Jin Hitonari.

98
00:07:35,610 --> 00:07:38,100
- I found him.
- What?

99
00:07:38,100 --> 00:07:42,780
He attended the Pig Farming Association party instead of me with my attendant.

100
00:07:46,150 --> 00:07:48,400
This is so much fun!

101
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:50,700
This is so much fun!

102
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:53,570
He got along so well with the people from the Pig Farming Association,

103
00:07:53,570 --> 00:07:56,570
that he drank and danced till he was drunk and passed out.

104
00:07:56,570 --> 00:07:59,570
Anyway, he's still asleep in the barn.

105
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:04,130
That's unbelievable.

106
00:08:04,130 --> 00:08:05,910
That's a relief.

107
00:08:07,470 --> 00:08:12,150
But... I have bad news.

108
00:08:14,090 --> 00:08:16,760
My staff has arrived.

109
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:19,390
So I have to go right now.

110
00:08:19,390 --> 00:08:22,270
I see. Is that so?

111
00:08:25,770 --> 00:08:30,960
♫ Try to forget it'll better ♫

112
00:08:34,740 --> 00:08:40,190
♫ Don't take that he says he will be better ♫

113
00:08:43,850 --> 00:08:48,830
♫ You always have a lot of ways ♫

114
00:08:48,830 --> 00:08:52,290
♫ Even if he's wrong ♫

115
00:08:53,370 --> 00:08:58,470
♫ Well, a good time doesn't last long ♫

116
00:08:59,630 --> 00:09:04,040
♫ Don't take it so hard ♫

117
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:09,330
♫ Like a strawberry scent that goes away ♫

118
00:09:09,810 --> 00:09:15,630
The weather is nice.

119
00:09:15,630 --> 00:09:20,600
[Grand Plaza Hotel]

120
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:24,960
♫ Time will be on your side ♫

121
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:31,300
♫ You need to come around to yourself ♫

122
00:09:31,300 --> 00:09:34,970
♫ One day it'll be ♫

123
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:40,400
I'm glad that everything worked out.

124
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:45,740
What did I say? Didn't I say everything would be fine?

125
00:09:45,740 --> 00:09:47,800
Where is your staff?

126
00:09:49,150 --> 00:09:51,410
They said they already arrived.

127
00:09:53,450 --> 00:09:56,560
- I should get going now.
- Miss Dali.

128
00:09:59,040 --> 00:10:03,660
Thank you for yesterday.

129
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:08,320
Thanks to you, I had fun as well.

130
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,810
Goodbye.

131
00:10:09,810 --> 00:10:11,290
Wait.

132
00:10:16,580 --> 00:10:19,180
Today and tomorrow, I will be very busy.

133
00:10:19,180 --> 00:10:21,840
It's an important deal, so there's a lot to review,

134
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:25,130
and before that, I have to visit other local livestock farms.

135
00:10:25,130 --> 00:10:27,670
I have to leave Amsterdam the day after tomorrow morning,

136
00:10:27,670 --> 00:10:31,960
because I bought a round-trip plane ticket in advance.

137
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:35,010
I have meetings one after another even after arriving in Korea.

138
00:10:35,010 --> 00:10:38,130
I also have to give reports about the contract.

139
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,730
That's my situation.

140
00:10:44,980 --> 00:10:47,050
That's too bad.

141
00:10:47,050 --> 00:10:52,550
If you had some free time, you would have been able to experience a little more of the beautiful places in the Netherlands.

142
00:10:52,550 --> 00:10:55,390
But I will be sure to visit the art museum.

143
00:10:55,390 --> 00:10:56,530
Sorry?

144
00:10:56,530 --> 00:10:58,700
I'm going to make time...

145
00:10:58,700 --> 00:11:01,080
to visit the art museum somehow.

146
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:06,320
I'm going to see those impressionist paintings that Korean people love so much.

147
00:11:06,320 --> 00:11:09,670
Then I'm going to visit that cafeteria that serves good food, although they are not as skilled as I am.

148
00:11:09,670 --> 00:11:11,230
And...

149
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:16,510
And see you, too.

150
00:11:17,530 --> 00:11:19,520
♫ You made me laugh ♫

151
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:22,570
Yes, please do.

152
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:28,120
I'm definitely going, so you have to wait for me. All right?

153
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:29,970
You have to. Please!

154
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:32,940
Then, goodbye.

155
00:11:33,580 --> 00:11:35,090
Wait.

156
00:11:35,980 --> 00:11:42,140
♫ When your scent gently spreads around me ♫

157
00:11:42,140 --> 00:11:44,950
Mr. Jin?

158
00:11:44,950 --> 00:11:48,610
♫ Everything in the world is ♫

159
00:11:48,610 --> 00:11:51,010
This watch is very important to me.

160
00:11:51,010 --> 00:11:53,750
So make sure to bring it with you when we see each other again.

161
00:11:53,750 --> 00:11:55,790
Make sure to bring it, please.

162
00:11:55,790 --> 00:11:58,240
Mr. Jin.

163
00:11:58,240 --> 00:12:05,720
♫ It's strange how we met ♫

164
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:13,000
♫ How did I fall in love at first sight? ♫

165
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:20,970
♫ It must be a fate that is not easy to explain ♫

166
00:12:20,970 --> 00:12:22,410
I did it!

167
00:12:22,410 --> 00:12:30,630
♫ I'm the only one for you, I'll give you this love ♫

168
00:12:35,250 --> 00:12:37,670
Where did she say the art museum was?

169
00:12:37,670 --> 00:12:40,160
I don't even know her number.

170
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:45,310
Oh! Just a moment. Sorry, sorry.

171
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:42,370
Miss Dali.

172
00:13:46,830 --> 00:13:50,160
Woah! Watch where you're going!

173
00:13:51,090 --> 00:13:52,810
Miss Dali!

174
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:02,680
Miss Dali!

175
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:06,720
Miss Dali!

176
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:36,440
Here.

177
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:38,400
Here.

178
00:14:44,170 --> 00:14:48,710
How can you find someone without even knowing if it's their real name or fake name?

179
00:14:48,710 --> 00:14:53,180
You also said you went to her house. What's the name of the town?

180
00:14:53,180 --> 00:14:56,960
I drove there in the middle of the night, how would I know that?

181
00:14:58,510 --> 00:15:01,150
It is in Amsterdam, right?

182
00:15:02,180 --> 00:15:03,630
That...

183
00:15:18,620 --> 00:15:21,260
Did you perhaps dream all this?

184
00:15:21,260 --> 00:15:23,750
No!

185
00:15:23,750 --> 00:15:26,520
No, I—

186
00:15:26,520 --> 00:15:29,820
