187
00:15:29,820 --> 00:15:35,090
Right, I went to a party and put a hole in a painting worth 160 billion won.

188
00:15:36,150 --> 00:15:38,990
1,600 won?

189
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:43,600
Seriously? I said it was 160 billion won. 160 billion won! Billion!

190
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:44,800
Miss Dali!

191
00:15:44,830 --> 00:15:46,890
So, it was a dream.

192
00:15:48,490 --> 00:15:51,600
Wait, Director.

193
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:53,030
Where's your watch?

194
00:15:53,030 --> 00:15:54,140
What?

195
00:15:54,140 --> 00:15:56,530
Your wristwatch.

196
00:15:56,530 --> 00:16:00,520
- I told you to leave it because it's so valuable.
- She's wearing a hat with crow feathers.

197
00:16:00,520 --> 00:16:01,930
Oh, that.

198
00:16:01,930 --> 00:16:06,130
No, why? What's the matter? She could have passed by!

199
00:16:06,130 --> 00:16:09,500
Don't tell me it was that girl.

200
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:11,190
[National Museum]

201
00:16:11,190 --> 00:16:13,880
- She has a hat with a crow feather on top.
- I'm sorry, I don't–

202
00:16:13,880 --> 00:16:17,500
She only says incredibly smart things that are hard for you to understand, right?

203
00:16:17,500 --> 00:16:18,860
How did you know?

204
00:16:18,860 --> 00:16:22,140
And she laughed at everything you said.

205
00:16:22,140 --> 00:16:23,030
Yes.

206
00:16:23,030 --> 00:16:25,510
She doesn't seem like it, but she can calculate things really quickly, right?

207
00:16:25,510 --> 00:16:26,750
Yes, that's what happened.

208
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:31,350
In technical terms, we call women like her thieves.
[St. Müller Kunst Galerig]

209
00:16:31,350 --> 00:16:34,660
- You're saying she left?
- I'm sorry I can't be of more help.

210
00:16:34,660 --> 00:16:39,460
Does it make sense that she'd quit her job and disappear because of one watch?

211
00:16:39,460 --> 00:16:43,520
She could if the watch was worth several hundred million won.

212
00:16:43,520 --> 00:16:46,180
But she was crying in front of the hotel.

213
00:16:46,180 --> 00:16:49,120
That's acting, of course!

214
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:52,470
No, she isn't that kind of person.

215
00:16:52,470 --> 00:16:56,250
There has to be some kind of reason.

216
00:16:56,250 --> 00:17:00,160
There's no such thing as an merciless thief in this world.

217
00:17:03,240 --> 00:17:07,390
Mr. Jin, you are so funny.

218
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:16,920
When others do you a favor, just saying thank you is enough.

219
00:17:18,460 --> 00:17:20,680
It wasn't any sort of fate.

220
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:26,610
According to the Mahayana Buddhist Vinaya Sutra, three thousand kalpas have gone by for us to meet.

221
00:17:26,610 --> 00:17:30,050
That's how precious our connection is.

222
00:17:35,040 --> 00:17:38,960
How dare you deceive Jin Moo Hak?

223
00:17:40,450 --> 00:17:44,760
Just wait till I catch you, you're dead.

224
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:47,440
You die!

