255
00:20:06,520 --> 00:20:08,920
Who is being so unreasonable...?

256
00:20:10,990 --> 00:20:14,260
"I pray for the well-being of the deceased."

257
00:20:14,260 --> 00:20:20,060
That is what you say when you can't think of condolences to say to the bereaved family in grief.

258
00:20:20,060 --> 00:20:21,880
If you don't know, memorize it.

259
00:20:25,590 --> 00:20:29,290
I'm sorry.

260
00:21:05,130 --> 00:21:08,060
I pray for the well-being of the deceased.

261
00:21:09,870 --> 00:21:12,460
Thank you for coming.

262
00:21:25,530 --> 00:21:27,930
That's Century Group's Director, Jang Tae Jin, right?

263
00:21:27,930 --> 00:21:30,330
How dare he come here.

264
00:21:30,330 --> 00:21:32,420
Why? Did something happen?

265
00:21:32,420 --> 00:21:36,880
He was going to marry the director's daughter...

266
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:38,960
People can hear you!

267
00:21:54,360 --> 00:21:56,100
Director.

268
00:22:10,380 --> 00:22:14,530
It's a lie, right? Tell me it's a lie.

269
00:22:16,940 --> 00:22:19,240
Tell me it's a lie...

270
00:22:26,860 --> 00:22:28,420
It's okay.

271
00:22:43,050 --> 00:22:44,610
It's okay.

272
00:22:53,630 --> 00:22:57,130
It seems that more mourners will be coming in. Please take care of it so that the family does not have to concern themselves about it.

273
00:22:57,130 --> 00:22:59,410
Yes, I will take care of it.

274
00:22:59,410 --> 00:23:03,110
Also, I would like to know more about the financial situation of the Cheongsong Art Museum.

275
00:23:06,030 --> 00:23:07,470
Discreetly.

276
00:23:07,470 --> 00:23:09,080
I understand, sir.

277
00:23:29,850 --> 00:23:31,530
Director.

278
00:23:32,780 --> 00:23:34,350
Director!

279
00:23:46,100 --> 00:23:49,970
- Father.
- What are you thinking about that's making you lose your mind?

280
00:23:49,970 --> 00:23:52,540
No, it's just that...

281
00:23:52,540 --> 00:23:56,030
I have lots of things to think about.

282
00:23:56,030 --> 00:23:59,010
Moo Hak hasn't come to work yet.

283
00:23:59,010 --> 00:24:04,630
He must've felt fatigued. He's been so busy preparing for the Netherlands.

284
00:24:04,630 --> 00:24:08,820
Don't worry too much. He said he'll be back to work tomorrow.

285
00:24:09,360 --> 00:24:15,470
Which art museum was it again?

286
00:24:16,470 --> 00:24:20,110
- Pardon?
- I'm talking about the one Moo Hak lent money to.

287
00:24:20,110 --> 00:24:22,630
- Cheong...
- Why are you asking about that place?

288
00:24:23,740 --> 00:24:25,890
It's a legit place, right?

289
00:24:27,060 --> 00:24:30,260
I'm sure Moo Hak will look into it and take care of it.

290
00:24:30,260 --> 00:24:34,300
You know, Moo Hak is quite meticulous when it comes to money.

291
00:24:34,300 --> 00:24:36,260
Well, you're right.

292
00:24:37,830 --> 00:24:39,380
- Goodbye.
- Yes, yes.

293
00:25:13,030 --> 00:25:15,100
Three thousand eons?

294
00:25:16,010 --> 00:25:17,970
What a load of crap.

295
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:21,130
Are you going to be fooled,

296
00:25:21,130 --> 00:25:25,480
after being captivated by Buddha Confucius?

297
00:25:28,050 --> 00:25:30,900
Even with just the minute hand on that watch costs...

298
00:25:30,900 --> 00:25:35,420
how many bowls of gamjatang (Potato and pork stew) is that?

299
00:25:41,960 --> 00:25:44,130
Seriously, come on!

300
00:25:48,040 --> 00:25:52,250
No... no, no, no.

301
00:25:52,250 --> 00:25:56,050
In times like these, you have to eat and cheer up.

302
00:25:59,970 --> 00:26:04,170
Even if she's hiding in the North Pole, I'll strangle a penguin.

303
00:26:04,170 --> 00:26:07,430
And if she's hiding in the South Pole, I'll hit a polar bear in the stomach.

304
00:26:07,430 --> 00:26:11,380
I will undoubtedly find her. Undoubtedly!

305
00:26:11,380 --> 00:26:16,790
Polar bears live in the North Pole and penguins live in the South Pole.

306
00:26:17,310 --> 00:26:19,810
You scared me!

307
00:26:20,450 --> 00:26:23,700
Did you follow your sick boss home to point that out?

308
00:26:23,700 --> 00:26:26,230
I thought you couldn't even drink water

309
00:26:26,230 --> 00:26:30,490
because your voice sounded like it was dying, so I brought these for you to drink–

310
00:26:34,030 --> 00:26:38,070
Did someone die? Why would I starve?

311
00:26:38,070 --> 00:26:44,340
You're right. Why did I uselessly worry about you?

312
00:26:52,590 --> 00:26:56,290
- It looks good.
- How is the Netherlands thing going?

313
00:26:57,430 --> 00:27:00,040
About that...

314
00:27:02,530 --> 00:27:04,560
I mean, we paid so much for the deposit

315
00:27:04,560 --> 00:27:08,150
and the private investigator can't even find one person?

316
00:27:08,150 --> 00:27:10,280
That's how it is in the Netherlands.

317
00:27:10,280 --> 00:27:14,610
It's a place where they don't live in a fast-paced environment.

318
00:27:14,610 --> 00:27:17,200
Contact the private investigator again,

319
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:19,650
and tell them if they find her, we'll give them ten times the deposit.

320
00:27:19,650 --> 00:27:21,440
All right. What?

321
00:27:21,440 --> 00:27:23,200
Ten times the deposit?

322
00:27:23,200 --> 00:27:25,540
I can't even bother him about it because I'm not there,

323
00:27:25,540 --> 00:27:29,620
so that amount of money will incentivize him to get to work. Right?

324
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:36,900
I'm asking because I'm really just curious,

325
00:27:39,190 --> 00:27:42,970
but do you want to find that watch or that woman?

326
00:27:42,970 --> 00:27:45,390
Of course, it's...

327
00:27:51,020 --> 00:27:52,420
the watch!

328
00:27:52,420 --> 00:27:57,220
Of course, it is. I misunderstood.

329
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:27,620
Have you asked the bank about postponing the loan repayment date yet?

330
00:28:28,210 --> 00:28:32,190
About that... everyone was so busy,

331
00:28:32,190 --> 00:28:34,500
so I decided to go back again today.

332
00:28:34,500 --> 00:28:38,110
So far, this is the status of the loan we identified.

333
00:28:38,110 --> 00:28:42,230
This financial situation is much worse than I expected.

334
00:28:43,050 --> 00:28:46,130
I've heard that running an art museum is like pouring water into a bottomless jar,

335
00:28:46,130 --> 00:28:50,440
but I didn't think it would be this bad.

336
00:28:51,260 --> 00:28:55,190
He gave all his wealth back to society,

337
00:28:55,190 --> 00:28:59,630
but he was actually confined to a museum full of debt.

338
00:28:59,630 --> 00:29:03,620
And in this big house, he didn't hire anyone to help out with it.

339
00:29:05,790 --> 00:29:09,410
He was my friend for 40 years, but

340
00:29:09,410 --> 00:29:14,390
I don't know whether to respect him or say he's a fool.

341
00:29:15,160 --> 00:29:18,030
He was such a foolish person.

342
00:29:21,020 --> 00:29:25,060
I'm thinking of dissolving all of my assets except for the art museum,

343
00:29:25,060 --> 00:29:27,340
including this house.

344
00:29:27,990 --> 00:29:31,080
Lawyer Cha, if you could find the right buyer...

345
00:29:31,080 --> 00:29:35,020
Trying to sell real estate with development restrictions won't work.

346
00:29:35,020 --> 00:29:38,420
Besides, all of that was already secured by the bank.

347
00:29:39,460 --> 00:29:44,500
The inheritance tax will come out soon. Do you have any countermeasures for that?

348
00:29:47,630 --> 00:29:49,680
If it comes to it,

349
00:29:50,170 --> 00:29:53,440
you might have to give up your inheritance.

350
00:30:05,310 --> 00:30:07,650
Where are you going when you're still sick?

351
00:30:07,650 --> 00:30:11,520
I have to stop by the hospital, and I have things to take care of at the bank.

352
00:30:11,520 --> 00:30:14,670
If it's an errand at the bank, you could just tell me to do it.

353
00:30:14,670 --> 00:30:18,320
It's my personal business, so why would I tell you to do it?

354
00:30:21,750 --> 00:30:24,540
How would I trust you?

355
00:30:34,460 --> 00:30:36,370
I'm doing this out of urgency.

356
00:30:36,370 --> 00:30:40,830
The repayment date is coming up, but I haven't been able to see him or get in contact with him.

357
00:30:40,830 --> 00:30:46,380
If you let me know where he is, I will go find him myself. I'm begging you, please.

358
00:30:46,380 --> 00:30:51,440
- The branch manager is not in Korea right now.
- Pardon?

359
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:55,830
He went to South Africa to attend the International Financial Symposium, so he won't be back here for a while.

360
00:30:55,830 --> 00:30:58,930
You see, he's going to Stockholm right after his stay in South Africa.

361
00:30:58,930 --> 00:31:00,820
Because of the global economic forum.

362
00:31:00,820 --> 00:31:05,190
Also, he said he was going to New York for his daughter's wedding,

363
00:31:05,190 --> 00:31:08,100
so I also don't know when he'll be returning.

364
00:31:19,480 --> 00:31:21,380
Sir.

365
00:31:22,740 --> 00:31:25,110
Dali!

366
00:31:25,110 --> 00:31:28,120
When did he return to Korea...

367
00:31:32,150 --> 00:31:37,630
So far, we've never been late on our interest and my credit rating is not bad.

368
00:31:37,630 --> 00:31:40,970
If you ask me to repay you so suddenly...

369
00:31:41,650 --> 00:31:44,350
Please help me this one time.

370
00:31:44,350 --> 00:31:47,980
I'll do whatever I can to resolve it quickly, so—

371
00:31:50,310 --> 00:31:52,330
Sir!

372
00:31:52,330 --> 00:31:55,770
Let me ask you for a favor, Dali.

373
00:31:55,770 --> 00:31:58,390
Please save me.

374
00:31:58,390 --> 00:32:02,080
I think I'm about to die right now because of your father.

375
00:32:02,080 --> 00:32:07,190
The credit rating is not the problem. Your father was your credit.

376
00:32:07,190 --> 00:32:11,790
But your father died! Without telling me.

377
00:32:11,790 --> 00:32:16,090
There are rumors that the Cheongsong Art Museum is being handed over.

378
00:32:16,640 --> 00:32:21,870
Even if we put everything else aside, let's address our bank issues first. Okay?

379
00:32:22,430 --> 00:32:25,250
We have to do that no matter what!

380
00:32:26,480 --> 00:32:31,300
Dali... are we strangers?

381
00:32:31,300 --> 00:32:35,270
I'm your father's friend.

382
00:32:35,270 --> 00:32:40,850
Dali... please, please save me.

383
00:33:05,660 --> 00:33:08,180
Did you come to the bank to update your bankbook?

384
00:33:08,180 --> 00:33:10,720
I said to turn your head away.

385
00:33:11,650 --> 00:33:16,460
In a world where one bank app can do transactions, account transfers, and currency exchange,

386
00:33:16,460 --> 00:33:20,550
what are paper bankbooks?

387
00:33:20,550 --> 00:33:23,130
Money is only money when you can touch it with your hands,

388
00:33:23,130 --> 00:33:27,080
see it with your eyes, and stamped it with numbers.

389
00:33:27,080 --> 00:33:30,110
And if I get hacked, will you take responsibility?

390
00:33:30,110 --> 00:33:32,380
How can someone who is so suspicious and wary

391
00:33:32,380 --> 00:33:37,130
fall for an unknown woman and lose that expensive watch?

392
00:33:37,130 --> 00:33:40,410
What do you mean, I fell for her?

393
00:33:41,300 --> 00:33:43,090
All right.

394
00:34:16,810 --> 00:34:19,360
I didn't get the monthly rent again!

395
00:34:19,360 --> 00:34:20,920
Was she pretty?

396
00:34:20,920 --> 00:34:22,290
What?

397
00:34:22,290 --> 00:34:25,790
I'm asking if she was pretty, that Netherlands woman.

398
00:34:25,790 --> 00:34:28,280
I keep telling you it wasn't like that.

399
00:34:29,410 --> 00:34:32,140
That means her body must've been amazing.

400
00:34:32,140 --> 00:34:33,730
I told you it wasn't like that!

401
00:34:33,730 --> 00:34:37,510
If it's not that too, were you drugged with something like sleeping pills?

402
00:34:37,510 --> 00:34:39,540
Really?

403
00:34:39,540 --> 00:34:40,890
Then, what is it?

404
00:34:40,890 --> 00:34:44,210
How the hell does someone get set up

405
00:34:44,210 --> 00:34:46,550
to lose their watch and not even know it?

406
00:34:46,550 --> 00:34:48,450
As long as you're not crazy,

407
00:34:48,450 --> 00:34:53,070
you probably wouldn't have put it on her wrist yourself. Right?

408
00:34:54,990 --> 00:34:56,420
Then, goodbye.

409
00:34:56,420 --> 00:34:57,820
Wait.

410
00:35:06,060 --> 00:35:09,100
Mr. Jin?

411
00:35:09,100 --> 00:35:11,530
This watch is very important to me.

412
00:35:11,530 --> 00:35:14,270
So make sure to bring it with you when we see each other again.

413
00:35:14,270 --> 00:35:16,310
Make sure to bring it, please.

414
00:35:17,550 --> 00:35:20,520
That's... right.

415
00:35:21,140 --> 00:35:23,140
As long as you're not crazy...

416
00:35:26,190 --> 00:35:31,660
♫ A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H, I, J ♫

417
00:35:31,660 --> 00:35:36,250
♫ K, L, M, N, O, P ♫

418
00:35:37,260 --> 00:35:39,780
♫ Q, R, S, T, U, V ♫

419
00:35:39,780 --> 00:35:42,150
What is it?

420
00:35:42,150 --> 00:35:44,080
It's nothing. It's nothing.

421
00:35:44,080 --> 00:35:46,310
I thought I saw something.

422
00:35:47,700 --> 00:35:50,600
Do you think that woman could be in Korea?

423
00:35:50,600 --> 00:35:52,110
No way.

424
00:35:52,110 --> 00:35:55,000
If you're going to flee, it's best to flee abroad.

425
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:56,800
That's true.

426
00:36:00,050 --> 00:36:04,690
Detective, he hit me first after getting drunk.

427
00:36:05,500 --> 00:36:09,160
Detective!

428
00:36:09,160 --> 00:36:11,930
That punk–

429
00:36:11,930 --> 00:36:14,200
You always do this

430
00:36:14,200 --> 00:36:16,300
when you drink.

431
00:36:16,300 --> 00:36:18,250
Quiet down!

432
00:36:18,250 --> 00:36:19,960
Do I look like a married woman to you?

433
00:36:19,960 --> 00:36:22,030
Sit down!

434
00:36:22,030 --> 00:36:23,880
Aren't you a married woman?

435
00:36:23,880 --> 00:36:27,310
- What is he saying?
- That's enough.

436
00:36:27,310 --> 00:36:30,760
I'm here to see Joo Won Tak.

437
00:36:30,760 --> 00:36:32,790
BE QUIET!

438
00:36:33,580 --> 00:36:35,090
What did you say?

439
00:36:35,090 --> 00:36:37,560
- I'm here to see Joo Won Tak.
- Oh.

440
00:36:37,560 --> 00:36:40,170
Detective Joo is off duty today. Did you come without calling him?

441
00:36:40,170 --> 00:36:43,620
I don't have his contact information. I just heard that he works here.

442
00:36:43,620 --> 00:36:45,500
Come back tomorrow.

443
00:36:45,500 --> 00:36:49,250
Or leave your contact information here.

444
00:36:50,910 --> 00:36:52,480
Excuse me.

445
00:36:55,260 --> 00:36:57,390
Try getting in touch with him here.

446
00:36:57,390 --> 00:37:01,410
He hasn't been eating or sleeping since the director passed.

447
00:37:01,410 --> 00:37:03,740
He might die at this rate.

448
00:37:05,620 --> 00:37:07,320
- Thank you.
- Sure.

449
00:37:12,470 --> 00:37:16,550
How can you give away his information when you don't even know her?

450
00:37:16,550 --> 00:37:18,020
You punk.

451
00:37:21,490 --> 00:37:23,100
Look.

452
00:37:24,190 --> 00:37:27,120
Oh, this is her? That goddess?

453
00:37:27,120 --> 00:37:29,660
That's right, punk.

454
00:37:29,660 --> 00:37:31,890
Wow, she's pretty!

455
00:37:31,890 --> 00:37:34,520
Sir, please sit down.

456
00:38:03,130 --> 00:38:08,950
Why didn't you get an IV vitamin treatment while you were at the hospital? It doesn't cost that much.

457
00:38:08,950 --> 00:38:11,810
I didn't get it because I don't need it.

458
00:38:11,810 --> 00:38:13,950
Do you think I wouldn't get it because of the cost?

459
00:38:13,950 --> 00:38:16,810
I think that's exactly why you didn't get it.

460
00:38:17,870 --> 00:38:23,130
Then again, you did lose an incredibly expensive watch, so you should be saving every penny.

461
00:38:23,130 --> 00:38:25,630
Why do you need to keep bringing it up? It's annoying.

462
00:38:25,630 --> 00:38:27,430
I'm going to find it!

463
00:38:27,430 --> 00:38:30,390
Even if I have to go to the end of the world,

464
00:38:30,390 --> 00:38:33,610
I'll find it no matter what!

465
00:38:36,900 --> 00:38:39,100
Drop me off up here and go home.

466
00:38:39,100 --> 00:38:41,000
Why? I can drop you off at your house.

467
00:38:41,020 --> 00:38:43,970
No. I need to stop by the pharmacy.

468
00:39:30,040 --> 00:39:32,340
[Don't be late on rent! Don't forget the rent! Remember the rent!]

469
00:39:56,330 --> 00:39:58,380
It's you again?

470
00:39:58,380 --> 00:40:00,670
How is it that a student like you is at the police station

471
00:40:00,670 --> 00:40:03,690
more often than at school?

472
00:40:03,690 --> 00:40:05,440
Taxpayers made it possible

473
00:40:05,440 --> 00:40:08,560
for you to receive food and shelter at the children's home.

474
00:40:08,560 --> 00:40:10,810
You should be grateful and live quietly.

475
00:40:10,810 --> 00:40:13,170
It's because of kids like you that

476
00:40:13,170 --> 00:40:16,130
orphans get a bad reputation.

477
00:40:16,130 --> 00:40:19,250
That you end up like this because there's no one to teach you any better.

478
00:40:19,250 --> 00:40:23,150
Ha. Look at this orphan bastard's eyes.

479
00:40:23,150 --> 00:40:27,710
- Lower your eyes. I said, lower your eyes!
- Hey!

480
00:40:31,370 --> 00:40:33,860
Who are you?

481
00:40:33,860 --> 00:40:36,300
Knives aren't the only things that can cut people.

482
00:40:36,300 --> 00:40:38,490
The wounds made from words don't even heal.

483
00:40:38,490 --> 00:40:41,700
- It stays embedded in your heart forever.
- What?

484
00:40:41,700 --> 00:40:44,820
Why are you hurting him? Won Tak didn't do anything wrong.

485
00:40:44,820 --> 00:40:46,540
1, 2, 3, 4, 5. 5!

486
00:40:46,540 --> 00:40:50,390
If it's 5 against 1, obviously the 1 is the victim.

487
00:40:50,390 --> 00:40:54,550
If 5 people attack at once, you know it's not just a simple assault but a special assault, right?

488
00:40:54,550 --> 00:40:57,620
Detective, you just subjected a special assault victim

489
00:40:57,620 --> 00:41:00,210
to physical, mental, and verbal attacks.

490
00:41:00,210 --> 00:41:01,920
Don't erase the CCTV.

491
00:41:01,920 --> 00:41:05,540
I have it all recorded on my phone anyway.

492
00:41:06,370 --> 00:41:09,400
- Who the hell is this psycho?
- She's my daughter.

493
00:41:13,910 --> 00:41:14,920
Isn't he from the Cheongsong family?

494
00:41:14,920 --> 00:41:18,690
The Cheongsong family's Kim Nak Cheon?

495
00:41:20,480 --> 00:41:24,160
And this kid is my son.

496
00:41:28,510 --> 00:41:31,010
Hearing the situation,

497
00:41:31,010 --> 00:41:35,950
it seems these students were bothering a disabled student.

498
00:41:35,950 --> 00:41:39,780
My son saw that and tried to stop it, resulting in a fight.

499
00:41:41,350 --> 00:41:43,060
Is that right?

500
00:41:47,930 --> 00:41:50,740
I taught him that.

501
00:41:50,740 --> 00:41:53,580
That the fist is for defending the weak.

502
00:41:54,700 --> 00:41:57,540
Did I teach him wrong?

503
00:41:58,350 --> 00:42:01,360
I apologize, I didn't know who he was.

504
00:42:01,360 --> 00:42:04,000
I apologize for my actions.

505
00:42:04,690 --> 00:42:09,170
- Would you like to have a cup of tea over there with me?
- That's not right.

506
00:42:09,170 --> 00:42:12,380
You should be apologizing to my son.

507
00:42:12,380 --> 00:42:15,830
If you sincerely apologize, my son will

508
00:42:15,830 --> 00:42:17,600
accept it.

